{{Infobox language |name=Kiong Nai |nativename=Jiongnai |states=[[China]] |region=[[Jinxiu County]], [[Guangxi]] |speakers={{sigfig|1080|2}} |date=1999 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Hmong-Mien |fam2=[[Hmongic languages|Hmongic]] |fam3=[[She language|She]]–Jiongnai |iso3=pnu |glotto=jion1236 |glottorefname=Jiongnai Bunu |notice=IPA }}
'''Kiong Nai''' (or '''Jiongnai''', {{zh|炯奈}} ''jiǒngnài'') is a divergent [[Hmongic languages|Hmongic (Miao)]] language spoken in [[Jinxiu County]], [[Guangxi]], [[China]]. The speakers' [[Endonym|autonym]] is pronounced {{IPA|[kjɔŋ33 nai33]}} or {{IPA|[kjaŋ31 nɛ31]}}; ''kjɔŋ33'' means 'mountain', while ''nai33'' means 'people' (Meng 2001:1). Mao & Li (2002) believe it to be most closely related to [[She language|She]].
==Dialects== Mao & Li (2002) divide Jiongnai into two major dialects.
*'''Longhua 龙华''', spoken in Longhua 龙华村 of Changdong Township 长垌乡 *'''Liuxiang 六巷''', spoken in Liuxiang Township 六巷乡
Jiongnai is spoken in the following villages in 3 townships of [[Jinxiu Yao Autonomous County]], Guangxi (Mao & Li 2002:1). *''Liuxiang Township'' 六巷乡: Liuxiang 六巷, Mengtou 门头, Dadeng 大凳, Huangsang 黄桑, Xincun 新村, Gupu 古蒲 *''Changdong Township'' 长垌乡: Longhua 龙华, Nanzhou 南州, Dajing 大进 *''Luoxiang Township'' 罗香乡: Zhanger 丈二, Liutuan 六团, Luodan 罗丹
