{{Infobox language |name=Nocte |nativename= |states=[[India]] |ethnicity=[[Nocte people|Nocte]] |speakers=33,000 |date=2001 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Brahmaputran languages|Brahmaputran]] |fam3=[[Konyak languages|Konyak]] |fam4=Tangsa–Nocte |iso3=njb |glotto=noct1238 |glottorefname=Nocte Naga }}
'''Nocte''' is a [[Naga language]] of northeastern [[India]]. Dialects are Khapa, Laju, and Ponthai (Lamlak), and alternate names include Borduria, Jaipuria, Mohongia, Namsangia, Nocte, Nokte, and Paniduria (''[[Ethnologue]]'').
==Geographical distribution== According to ''Ethnologue'', Nocte is spoken in the following locations.
*Khonsa, Namsang, and Laju circles of [[Tirap district]], southeastern [[Arunachal Pradesh]] *[[Changlang district]], southeastern [[Arunachal Pradesh]] *Jaipur, [[Lakhimpur district]], [[Assam]] *Namsang, [[Mon district]], northern [[Nagaland]]
